Scott HICKS, Appellant, v. F. G. ZERBST, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Atlanta, Ga., Appellee. * No. 8595. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Oct. 12, 1937. Scott Hicks, in pro. per. Lawrence S. Camp, U. S. Atty., and, Harvey H. Tysinger and E. T. Nichols, Asst. U. S. Attys., all of Atlanta, Ga., for appellee.

Before FOSTER, SIBLEY, and HOLMES, Circuit Judges.

Writ of certiorari denied 58 S.Ct. 411, 82 L.Ed. —.

 PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
